# Network Classes

## Classful Address

![Classful Address](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20251015104624497420/classful_aaddress.webp)

The classful addressing system divides the IP address space into five classes: A, B, C, D, and E. Each class serves a different purpose and has its own range of addresses. The classes are defined by the leading bits of the IP address and can accommodate different types of networks and hosts.